Why Gleam
---

I have three main cases for why you should consider Gleam for your next project:
<!--pause-->
# The FP Noob

You want to learn more about functional programming but don't want to step into the world of monads and endofunctors ala Haskell.
<!--pause-->
## The Beam Enjoyer

You want to make use of the BEAM VM and the existing ecosystem of Erlang and Elixir packages, but you prefer the simplicity and style of C or Javascript.
<!--pause-->
### Any sane person

Lucy (The Gleam mascot) is just cute af.
![Lucy on a computer](./lucydebugfail.png)
